global education crisis with a
look at our

25:59.158 --> 26:04.630 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
New York public station WNET's
documentary
series "Time for School."

26:04.663 --> 26:09.868 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For 12 years, PBS has followed
six children
from around the world who are
simply trying

26:09.902 --> 26:11.670 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to get a basic education.

26:11.703 --> 26:17.376 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Tonight, we meet Raluca from
post-communist
Romania, whose parents have been
working long

26:17.409 --> 26:22.147 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
hours to give her every
opportunity in the
country's new free market
economy.

26:22.181 --> 26:29.588 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RALUCA IFRIMESCU, Romania
(through translator):
This is my bed where I sleep.
And this is

26:29.621 --> 26:32.925 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Sylvester, the cat that I sleep
with.

26:32.958 --> 26:41.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is the drawer where I keep
a lot of books.
And this is a book that shows
you everything

26:41.433 --> 26:49.541 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
about nature: the earth,
animals, people.
This book shows you everything.
You should

26:49.575 --> 26:56.281 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
buy it. And this is from my mom
and dad's
wedding. They're really
wonderful people for

26:56.315 --> 26:58.183 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
me.

26:58.217 --> 27:04.022 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NARRATOR: Raluca Ifrimescu is 8
years old
and lives in Bucharest, Romania,
with her

27:04.056 --> 27:05.791 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
