struggle for it.

27:12.664 --> 27:18.103 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NARRATOR: Though Raluca's family
seems to
enjoy a comfortable life,
economic security

27:18.136 --> 27:24.743 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is not something they take for
granted. Romania
is a work in progress. When
communism ended

27:24.776 --> 27:31.283 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in 1989, the country began a
transition to
capitalism.

27:31.316 --> 27:35.487 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Raluca's parents are trying to
give her every
opportunity to succeed in the
new free market

27:35.521 --> 27:44.096 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
economy, and they know the best
possible education
is essential. Her family can't
afford a baby-sitter,

27:44.129 --> 27:49.935 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
so Raluca commutes 45 minutes to
school on
her own every day to attend a
public school

27:49.968 --> 27:51.904 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
considered one of the finest in
Bucharest.

27:51.937 --> 27:54.907 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CRISTI IFRIMESCU (through
translator): (through
translator): She knows she's not
supposed

27:54.940 --> 27:56.708 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to talk to strangers.

27:56.742 --> 27:59.278 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MIRELA IFRIMESCU, Mother of
Raluca (through
translator): When she was in
kindergarten,

27:59.311 --> 28:04.550 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
